title: BADGER-DIP 1: Pause Negative Rebasing
body:
After much deliberation, a forum signaling vote, and a snapshot poll of DIGG holders, there has been support shown for pausing negative rebases.  A Yes vote here will signal support for respecting the result of these votes and move forward with the pausing negative rebases.

There are long term plans for DIGG that continue to be honed and worked on by the DIGG community and a forthcoming BIP is likely that will request the necessary resources (monetary or otherwise) to support its implementation.  In the interim a proposal was put forth to pause negative rebases and has passed through newly deployed DIGG Governance.  Badger is still ultimately the owner of DIGG so moving forward with the change requires BADGER governance approval.

**Forum Discussion (24 For / 11 Against):**  https://forum.badger.finance/t/dip-1-pause-negative-rebasing-of-digg/5008
**Snapshot Results (20.3 DIGG For / 11.3 DIGG Against):** https://snapshot.org/#/digg2.eth/proposal/QmUQqKnrcQ4wCWiYriARs3qiCxdRaGCERWhsAUP3T2x8RX
